padang-padang beach - one of bali's top surf spots warm waters, crowds of young backpackers, cheap living and reliable waves keep bali near the top of world surfing destinations. the southern coast at kuta, legian and canggu, the bukit peninsula and nusa lembongan are the primary draws. expert surfers usually head for the big breaks off the bukit peninsula, whilst beginners will find the gentler, sandy areas between kuta and legian to be ideal for learning. all bali's surf beaches are described in the "indo surf and lingo" surfing guidebook, together with free bali tide charts on their website [52]. 